.TH "imr_write" 9 "imr_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
imr_write \- write an IMR at a given index.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" imr_write
.BI "(struct imr_device *idev "  ","
.BI "u32 imr_id "  ","
.BI "struct imr_regs *imr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "idev" 12
pointer to imr_device structure.
.IP "imr_id" 12
IMR entry to write.
.IP "imr" 12
IMR structure representing address and access masks.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Requires caller to hold imr mutex.
Note lock bits need to be written independently of address bits.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or error code passed from mbi_iosf on failure.
